{
  "texts": [
    "This step was very important for the numbering step of the teeth.",
    "Because the success rate of the numbering process was found to be low in the first training without separating the right and left sides.",
    "For this purpose, a DenseNet CNN architecture was utilized, which was introduced in 2016 by Huang et al. [38].",
    "DenseNet architecture uses dense connections, which connect each layer to other layers in a forward manner.",
    "Dense connections have benefits, such as reducing model parameters, decreasing vanishing-gradient problem, encouraging feature reuse, and strengthening feature propagation along layers."
  ]
}